These free-text descriptions were subsequently examined by a doctor and, where possible, matched to entries in the coding tree. Free-text descriptions which could not be matched with very high probability have been marked as "unclassifiable".   Note that myasthenia gravis appears twice (under codes 1260 and 1437).
